So, just to recapitulate, this book is intended as a practical guide to how to go about the business of making private equity investments, whether at the company or (probably more usually) at the fund level. It attempts to describe reality as I, as a practitioner, have experienced it over the years, and to stick to the highways of the possible, not to explore the back lanes of intellectual perfection. Private equity investing is quite difficult enough already without getting distracted by largely irrelevant issues.

